multipleChoiceQuiz.question:
Questions 1-5

Do the following statements agree with the information given in Reading Passage 1?

In boxes 1-5 on your answer sheet, write

TRUE               if the statement agrees with the information

FALSE             if the statement contradicts the information

NOT GIVEN    if there is no information on this

quizzes.description: Cork bark should be stripped in dry atmospheric conditions.(4)
The cork oak has the thickest bark of any living tree.(1)
Scientists have developed a synthetic cork with the same cellular structures as natural cork.(2)
The only way to remove the bark from cork oak trees is by hand.(5)
Individual cork oak trees must be left for 25 years between the first and second harvest.(3)
